dc_description_s: This map layer shows tornado touchdown points in the United States, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands, from 1950 to 2004. Statistical data were obtained from the National Weather Service, Storm Prediction Center (SPC). The SPC data originate from the Severe Thunderstorm Database and the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) Storm Data publication. This layer is clipped to Pennsylvania
dc_creator_sm: National Weather Service, Storm Prediction Center
